        "discriminators": [
          "The classic ding-dong is two struck chime bars, so expect transient_count near 2 with a clean ring under and after them — a distinctive count for a bell.",
          "Tuned bars are less inharmonic than a cast bell, so inharmonicity sits below BELLS-LARGE and BELLS-HANDBELL, and the ring is shorter than a tower bell but much longer than a tiny BELLS-ANIMAL.",
          "A rasping door BUZZER is not a bell at all — that is ALARMS-BUZZER: sustained, distorted, no decay. The presence or absence of a decaying tail decides it outright.",
          "UCS keeps electronic doorbell chimes here too, which is what caps this at narrowable: a synthesized ding-dong has the envelope but not the inharmonic partials."
        ],
